The new electoral laws require voters to present an identity document with a photograph, as well as an American citizenship test.
On the other hand, those laws reduce periods of early voting, invalidate the right to vote as an elector on the day of election and withdraw their right to vote to citizens with criminal record.
Before the 2006 elections, no American state required voters to submit a photographed identity document.
