As far as local legislation is concerned, is it simpler than ours?
In general, I would not like to draw up a comparison without specific data. However, Germany remains a model in some respects, but it cannot be accurately defined in what is best.
Could it be better, for example, as regards the quality of inspectors?
I'm sure not, but, I repeat, I don't like to make these kind of comparisons.
It is necessary to say that even those countries that we take as a model must face a large number of problems.
