You can say, "We change the law and allow it," but you can't say that we will do as if nothing.
In the Public Procurement Act, legislation is quite strict as to how to act formally, and this is what it should be like to protect public competition.
But, on the other hand, it is tragic that the candidate is excluded with the best offer not to meet formal requirements.
The law will never be perfect, but its application must be correct. This is, in my opinion, what we lack.
