The required heating and cooling are obtained from geothermal energy.
Although the mountain of books is located under a huge glass pyramid, even on the sunny days the sun only shines for a few hours inside.
The huge wooden circles located cross-sectionally on the glass façade serve to give shade and absorb most of the sun's rays.
This creates a comfortable indoor climate.
The rest is the thing about automatic blinds.
